<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
    <head>
        <meta charset="UTF-8" />
        <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
        <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="ie=edge" />
        <link
            rel="stylesheet"
            type="text/css"
            media="screen"
            href="./../css/main.css"
        />
        <link
            rel="stylesheet"
            type="text/css"
            media="screen"
            href="./../css/appForm.css"
        />
        <title>Application Form</title>
    </head>
    <body>
        <div class="container card">
            <div class="form-padding">
            <div id="baseCampInfoContainer">
                <p class="header">Student Application Form</p>
                <p class="info-text">Base Camp Coding Academy</p>
                <p class="info-text">301 North Main Street</p>
                <p class="info-text">Water Valley, MS 38965</p>
                <a class="info-text" target="blank" href="http://www.basecampcodingacademy.org"
                    >http://www.basecampcodingacademy.org</a
                >
            </div>
            <p class="info-paragraph" id="infoBody">
                Thank you for applying to BCCA! This is the first step of a two
                part application process. Strong candidates will be contacted
                for an in-person interview, so make sure to check your email for
                follow-up! Base Camp is a targeted program for north Mississippi
                high school seniors able to live within driving distance of
                Water Valley.
            </p>
            <p class="info-paragraph" id="infoBody">
                Space at BCCA is very limited. This is a huge opportunity, and
                responsibility. Please help us understand why you are the right
                person to receive this opportunity. In order to be eligible to
                apply you must have first been nominated by a teacher, employer,
                or other qualified individual who can speak to your abilities.
            </p>
            <form id="applicationForm" method="POST" action="apply">
                <div class="formContainer" id="formPartOne">
                    <p class="requiredWord">* Required</p>
                    <p class="text">
                        Name:<span class="requiredAsterisk">*</span>
                    </p>
                    <input
                        name="name"
                        type="text"
                        placeholder="Your answer"
                        required
                    />
                    <p class="text">
                        Email Address:<span class="requiredAsterisk">*</span>
                    </p>
                    <input
                        name="email"
                        type="email"
                        placeholder="Your answer"
                        required
                    />
                    <p class="text">
                        School you currently attend:<span
                            class="requiredAsterisk"
                            >*</span
                        >
                    </p>
                    <input
                        name="school"
                        type="text"
                        placeholder="Your answer"
                        required
                    />
                    <p class="text">
                        Do you meet our eligibility requirements?<span
                            class="requiredAsterisk"
                            >*</span>
                            <br>
                            <span class="tiny-text">
                                Are you a high school senior? Have you been nominated?
                                Do you live in north Mississippi?
                            </span>
                    </p>
                    
                    
                    <label>
                        <input
                            class="formRadioButton"
                            id="radioButtonYes"
                            type="radio"
                            name="eligible"
                            value="true"
                            required
                        /> Yep, lets get started! </label
                    ><br /><br />
                    <label>
                        <input
                            class="formRadioButton"
                            id="radioButtonNo"
                            type="radio"
                            name="eligible"
                            value="false"
                        /> I don't think so.
                    </label>
                </div>
                <div class="formContainer hidden" id="formPartTwo">
                    <p class="text">Age:<span class="requiredAsterisk">*</span></p>
                    <input class="partTwoInput" placeholder="Your answer" name="age" type="number" />
                    <p class="text">Phone:<span class="requiredAsterisk" >*</span></p>
                    <input class="partTwoInput" placeholder="Your answer" name="phone" type="text" />
                    <p class="text">Graduation:<span class="requiredAsterisk">*</span></p>
                    <input class="partTwoInput" placeholder="Your answer" name="graduation" type="date" />
                    <div class="group-info">
                    <p class="text">What is your current plan for next year?<span class="requiredAsterisk">*</span>
                        <br><span class="tiny-text">What do you plan to do after you graduate high school if it were not for Base Camp?</span>
                    </p>
                    </div>
                    <textarea
                    placeholder="Your answer"
                    class="partTwoInput"
                    name="plans"
                    cols="30"
                    rows="10">
                    </textarea>
                    <div>
                            <p>Where Brown Banner Thing Will Go!</p>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <p class="tiny-text">For example, you might include times when you were able to think logically or creatively to solve a problem,
                             or when you overcame a challenging situation with school, work, or a project.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <p class="text">Aptitude:<span class="requiredAsterisk">*</span>
                        <br><span class="tiny-text">Please share a specific example of when you were a strong problem solver.</span>
                    </p>
                    <textarea
                    placeholder="Your answer"
                    class="partTwoInput"
                    name="aptitude"
                    cols="30"
                    rows="10"
                    ></textarea>
                    <p class="text">Dedication / Work Ethic / Heart:<span class="requiredAsterisk">*</span>
                        <br><span class="tiny-text">Please share a specific example of your dedication and work ethic.</span>
                    </p>
                    <textarea
                    placeholder="Your answer"
                    class="partTwoInput"
                    name="dedication"
                    cols="30"
                    rows="10"
                    ></textarea>
                    <p class="text">Passion / Persistence:<span class="requiredAsterisk">*</span>
                        <br><span class="tiny-text">Please tell us about something you are passionate about and have worked hard to achieve. 
                            This can be clubs, sports teams, hobbies, church groups, etc.</span>
                    </p>
                    <textarea
                    placeholder="Your answer"
                    class="partTwoInput"
                    name="passion"
                    cols="30"
                    rows="10"
                    ></textarea>
                    <br>
                    <p class="tiny-text">
                        Base Camp Coding Academy admits students of any race, color, national and ethnic origin to all the rights, privileges, programs, and activities generally accorded or made available to students at the school. It does not discriminate on the basis of race, color, national and ethnic origin in administration of its educational policies, admissions policies, scholarship and loan programs, and athletic and other school-administered programs.
                    </p>
                    <p class="text">Meeting Date:</p>
                    <input class="partTwoInput" placeholder="Your answer" name="meeting" type="date" />
                </div>
                <br>
                <button>Submit</button>
            </form>
            </div>
        </div>
        <script src="./../../javascript/formApply.js"></script>
    </body>
</html>
